H0.text: kg/s is the units that should be used for the density measurements when a researcher is measuring changes in the density of the upper atmosphere over time.

H1.text: m³/s is the units that should be used for measuring changes in the density of the upper atmosphere over time.

H2.text: L/m³ is the units that should be used for the density measurements of the upper atmosphere over time.

H3.text: kg/m³ is the appropriate units for measuring changes in the density of the upper atmosphere over time.

A4.text: The density of air or atmospheric density, denoted ρ, is the mass per unit volume of Earth's atmosphere at a given point and time.

A5.text: The standard sea level density of air at 101.325 kPa (abs) and 15 °C (59 °F) is 1.2250 kg/m3.
